caption.text:
The greatest Secret Boss in all of video games.

Climbing to the peak of Mt. Silver will go down as one of the most mysterious and hyped moments in all of Pokémon. What could be at the top? Is it a powerful TM? A Legendary Pokémon? I don't think anyone could have expected what was awaiting them.

Reaching the peak and seeing Red for the first time was both exhilarating and intimidating. His silence expressed more emotions than any words could. "Should I battle this trainer? Will they pose any challenge? Let's test his abilities". We all breeezed our way through Gold & Silver but Red was the first challenge a lot of us faced. Never again will we experience a secret boss as impeccable as Red.

What is your favorite Secret Boss in Video games? I would love to see it in the comments!
.
.
.

Here's a picture of @wickedcooltoys' Mewtwo figure! Even though the photo is a lot darker than what I usually post, I still wanted to put it on here. It's different! I really liked taking this picture, because even if it does not seem like it, it was raining a lot. 😂 Do not stop taking photos because of a storm, in fact, it's a great way to explore new styles! I hope you all have a nice week. 💕 Who got Link's Awakening? I know there are many of you who have already finished it so it must be great! I still haven't started it, because I had a lot of studying to do this week, so I did not really have the time. 😭 It'll have to wait a little bit more! 💖
The new amiibos too are sublime! I pre-ordered mine and I got them sent to my hometown. I know they arrived, but I'm only going to be there in two weeks so I have to wait a bit. 😅
Have a nice weekend and take care of yourself. 💖

Wibbly Wobbly....
The Gardens Between Review

The Gardens Between is an interesting time bending puzzle game. Rather than controling the movements of the 2 characters, you control time putting them both in the right place at the right time.

A great art style and subtle use of music and sound flow with you in your travels through odd structures littered with large everyday items which all serve a purpose, some more hidden than others. All said items link together and at the end of a level reveal memories the 2 characters have shared. The story while minimalist is well told and impactful when it all come together at the end.

I really enjoyed my time with #TheGardensBetween although the environments were a bit samey they are all well constructed I just wanted a little more variety however that is sort of answered in the end. In the end #TheGardensBetween is short but sweet, which left me wanting more, even a few additional levels would have been great.

preview_comments.text: I’ll probably end up getting this one too 🤷‍♂️

@prince_of_platinum that's mit even that long dude. Some games take longer to manufacture die to a lot of different reasons. My Last order on LRG for example took 9 months until they were able to ship.

@mortenneelsen part of the problem is that these “limited physical media” companies are quick to take your money day one without stating somewhat accurate shipping dates. I can understand 3-4 weeks, but by the time 3-4 months rolls around you either lose interest or forget about the game completely. Now I know I don’t have to order the product and it’s completely optional but I believe it would be a smarter business practice to reveal/announce/sell the item when they have product in hand, instead of announcing something new each month when orders are backed by up months. LRG has become a joke now with some of it’s wait times (I’m still waiting on a January 1st order!) These are also small businesses that are usually run by only a few people but I think they’re in over their heads when they keep announcing things way ahead of time.

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I recall the Game Boy being my first ever console or at least my mum let me nick it for long enough to call it that. I played the original Zelda Link's Awakening and HATED the Tektites and the remaster has me feeling no different!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The dungeon builder aspect has me excited! I've made and completed two of my own custom-made dungeons. I was really hoping the game would come with an online function where creators could send their dungeons to friends in an effort to test their metal but it doesn't seem to exist! The only way to do it is to scan a Link's Awakening Amiibo in and transfer the dungeon through that. Meaning only local sharing. How poop.
